WEBVTT

00:00:00.540 --> 00:00:02.240
Her records are a complete match.

00:00:02.240 --> 00:00:04.640
The body is that of Natsumi Hayase-san.

00:00:04.640 --> 00:00:07.650
Turn yourself in, and you'll be framed
for both their deaths.

00:00:07.650 --> 00:00:09.880
You'll be leaving your only child behind.

00:00:09.880 --> 00:00:12.020
What should I...

00:00:12.020 --> 00:00:13.130
You must reboot.

00:00:13.130 --> 00:00:16.750
I can make you into Gido.

00:00:18.620 --> 00:00:23.500
I've rebooted as the man
who murdered my wife.

00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:28.290
We won't know
unless we find whoever killed Gido.

00:00:28.290 --> 00:00:30.590
I know you're not my husband.

00:00:30.590 --> 00:00:33.480
You are Riku Hayase-san, are you not?

00:00:33.480 --> 00:00:36.750
- Gido called me today.
- Today?

00:00:36.750 --> 00:00:38.380
But that wasn't "you."

00:00:38.380 --> 00:00:40.550
That was the real Gido.

00:00:40.550 --> 00:00:44.560
Gido... is still alive?

00:00:45.670 --> 00:00:48.500
[Ayumi Gido, Reboot, Day 4]

00:00:50.400 --> 00:00:52.790
If Gido is alive,

00:00:52.790 --> 00:00:56.780
I can prove I'm innocent.

00:00:56.780 --> 00:01:02.150
No, can I truly trust her?

00:01:02.150 --> 00:01:05.980
Ridiculous. I am Ayumi Gido. Leave.

00:01:05.980 --> 00:01:08.730
Then I'll call the police here, right now.

00:01:09.590 --> 00:01:12.830
You're a wanted man, are you not?

00:01:15.470 --> 00:01:18.680
Will you admit you're Riku Hayase?

00:01:20.440 --> 00:01:21.460
I'm reporting you.

00:01:21.460 --> 00:01:23.190
Fine.

00:01:25.490 --> 00:01:27.210
I admit it.

00:01:32.040 --> 00:01:34.350
Where is Gido?

00:01:35.750 --> 00:01:38.520
You know where he is, don't you?

00:01:39.800 --> 00:01:41.810
I'm sorry.

00:01:42.720 --> 00:01:44.690
Your husband is dead.

00:01:46.720 --> 00:01:47.750
What?

00:01:47.750 --> 00:01:50.170
Someone stabbed him.

00:01:50.170 --> 00:01:52.140
He was buried deep in a forest.

00:01:52.140 --> 00:01:54.940
Impossible. He called me earlier today.

00:01:54.940 --> 00:01:58.120
Anyone can fake a voice over the phone.

00:01:58.120 --> 00:02:01.310
You're not exactly convincing me.

00:02:08.080 --> 00:02:10.330
Take me there.

00:02:10.330 --> 00:02:12.210
Show me where he was buried.

00:02:22.450 --> 00:02:32.440
Timing and subtitles by
"🍰 The Pastry Detectives 🔍" Team @Viki.com

00:02:32.440 --> 00:02:33.530
I'll take over.

00:02:33.530 --> 00:02:35.620
No, let me.

00:02:43.620 --> 00:02:46.150
Are you sure this is the spot?

00:02:46.150 --> 00:02:48.930
I tripped over that very tree.

00:02:48.930 --> 00:02:51.390
I'm certain this is where he is.

00:02:58.010 --> 00:03:00.970
- I've got this—
- The sooner we're out of here, the better.

00:03:01.650 --> 00:03:03.770
And it wouldn't sit well with me

00:03:03.770 --> 00:03:06.960
knowing I made a wife unearth her husband.

00:03:08.740 --> 00:03:12.250
Why are you pretending to be Gido?

00:03:16.230 --> 00:03:18.760
Trying to get away with murder?

00:03:21.280 --> 00:03:23.430
I murdered no one.

00:03:24.410 --> 00:03:26.470
Then who killed your wife?

00:03:27.390 --> 00:03:28.510
[Natsumi Hayase]

00:03:28.510 --> 00:03:31.330
Gido, he really did...

00:03:55.210 --> 00:03:57.910
I would stop there if I were you.

00:04:03.640 --> 00:04:05.720
It's not him.

00:04:12.330 --> 00:04:14.130
This isn't Gido.

00:04:14.130 --> 00:04:15.580
That's...

00:04:15.580 --> 00:04:18.320
Sir, I never touched the money -

00:04:18.320 --> 00:04:20.460
This man was named Ando.

00:04:20.460 --> 00:04:23.010
He was killed in front of my very eyes.

00:04:24.700 --> 00:04:26.890
Killed?

00:04:29.940 --> 00:04:31.810
Hide!

00:04:36.570 --> 00:04:38.050
Hurry!

00:04:42.530 --> 00:04:45.050
Turn around.

00:04:48.050 --> 00:04:50.270
Gido-san?

00:04:50.270 --> 00:04:53.840
What're you doing out here?

00:04:56.180 --> 00:05:02.210
Checking to see if I'm getting the job done?

00:05:02.210 --> 00:05:03.960
Yes.

00:05:04.760 --> 00:05:07.530
Goroku's orders, right?

00:05:07.530 --> 00:05:09.610
Damn, he should trust me.

00:05:09.610 --> 00:05:12.420
I'm a diligent worker!

00:05:12.420 --> 00:05:14.150
Looks like it.

00:05:14.150 --> 00:05:19.570
But thanks for digging a hole for me.

00:05:26.800 --> 00:05:27.830
Heavy?

00:05:27.830 --> 00:05:30.840
Yes, this one's a real load.

00:05:30.840 --> 00:05:34.850
Any reason you're still sticking around?

00:05:34.850 --> 00:05:36.920
I'll bury the body, promise.

00:05:36.920 --> 00:05:38.530
Right, you get to that.

00:05:38.530 --> 00:05:41.760
Already on it, Sir.

00:05:53.450 --> 00:05:55.420
- What's going on?
- Hide yourself.

00:05:55.420 --> 00:05:57.070
I don't understand.

00:05:57.070 --> 00:05:59.880
What was Gido doing?

00:05:59.880 --> 00:06:01.010
Where is he?

00:06:01.010 --> 00:06:03.110
Calm down.

00:06:19.750 --> 00:06:22.190
You haven't eaten, have you?

00:06:27.520 --> 00:06:29.930
Forget everything I told you.

00:06:29.930 --> 00:06:32.430
You'll only get yourself involved.

00:06:33.820 --> 00:06:38.220
I'd advise you to forget about Gido as well.

00:06:40.140 --> 00:06:42.900
Gido is no murderer.

00:06:45.050 --> 00:06:48.650
Given what I know, I would say otherwise.

00:06:49.640 --> 00:06:54.850
My husband was an upstanding officer.

00:07:00.110 --> 00:07:03.120
You haven't seen him in years, have you?

00:07:05.260 --> 00:07:08.820
You couldn't have known everything about him.

00:07:14.350 --> 00:07:17.240
I'm sorry.

00:07:18.290 --> 00:07:21.100
I shouldn't speak like a know-it-all.

00:07:21.100 --> 00:07:23.310
Especially when I'm in a similar situation.

00:07:24.360 --> 00:07:27.410
I knew nothing about my wife.

00:07:28.470 --> 00:07:31.590
I didn't know she had ties
to a dangerous organization.

00:07:33.580 --> 00:07:37.410
I will regret my ignorance
until the day I die.

00:07:41.360 --> 00:07:44.820
I understand your hatred for Gido.

00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:51.750
But I will choose to believe my husband.

00:07:56.240 --> 00:08:01.990
If I may ask, why were you two living apart?

00:08:06.470 --> 00:08:08.850
I believe it was the fire.

00:08:08.850 --> 00:08:13.140
He didn't help around the house*?
(*"Fire" and "chores" sound similar)

00:08:16.420 --> 00:08:20.630
No, I burnt our home down.

00:08:20.630 --> 00:08:24.940
It also affected the home next door.

00:08:24.940 --> 00:08:30.180
We moved to an older apartment,
to better pay reparations.

00:08:30.980 --> 00:08:34.870
Gido blamed you?

00:08:37.460 --> 00:08:39.550
No, not even once.

00:08:39.550 --> 00:08:43.590
My husband may seem rough,

00:08:43.590 --> 00:08:46.420
but he's a kind man at heart.

00:08:50.370 --> 00:08:53.290
He helped pay for reparations,

00:08:53.290 --> 00:08:57.120
even when we lived apart.

00:08:58.970 --> 00:09:01.430
That may be

00:09:01.430 --> 00:09:07.130
why he got involved in shady business.

00:09:07.130 --> 00:09:09.800
He chose to get involved of his own accord.

00:09:09.800 --> 00:09:12.010
You're not responsible for his fate.

00:09:19.050 --> 00:09:21.940
Was my husband truly dead?

00:09:24.370 --> 00:09:26.670
When I saw him, he was still breathing.

00:09:26.670 --> 00:09:28.780
- Gido!
- Who buried him?

00:09:28.780 --> 00:09:30.340
A woman named Ichika-san.

00:09:30.340 --> 00:09:33.550
I only watched from afar.

00:09:33.550 --> 00:09:37.340
Then it's entirely possible he's still alive.

00:09:37.340 --> 00:09:39.810
- You didn't check for yourself.
- But Ichika-san...

00:09:39.810 --> 00:09:42.470
She may be lying to you.

00:09:44.260 --> 00:09:47.460
You think she tricked me?

00:09:47.460 --> 00:09:49.550
No, I don't believe she would.

00:09:49.550 --> 00:09:51.920
How can you be sure?

00:09:51.920 --> 00:09:53.930
She's...

00:09:55.350 --> 00:09:58.030
She's kind to my family.

00:09:58.030 --> 00:10:01.900
She blissfully enjoys desserts as well.

00:10:02.610 --> 00:10:05.090
That alone is enough to convince you?

00:10:05.090 --> 00:10:10.800
I just don't think she's a bad person.

00:10:10.800 --> 00:10:13.000
Call it a pâtissier's hunch.

00:10:18.720 --> 00:10:22.970
Please don't tell this Ichika-san
about my husband.

00:10:22.970 --> 00:10:24.020
Why not?

00:10:24.020 --> 00:10:27.600
I want you to look into her
while she still trusts you.

00:10:27.600 --> 00:10:28.990
What?

00:10:28.990 --> 00:10:33.690
She's lying to you.

00:10:35.680 --> 00:10:37.630
That's the hunch I have.

00:11:26.700 --> 00:11:29.110
I'll be back.

00:11:43.080 --> 00:11:45.750
Can I have a bite?

00:11:45.750 --> 00:11:47.940
No. Your doctor would scold me.

00:11:47.940 --> 00:11:50.720
What, you're just gonna flaunt your burger?

00:11:52.840 --> 00:11:55.040
Ew, gross!

00:11:55.040 --> 00:11:58.300
You're such a bully.

00:11:59.030 --> 00:12:01.810
I'll ask the doctor about it for next time.

00:12:01.810 --> 00:12:03.310
- Really?
- Yes.

00:12:03.310 --> 00:12:06.690
Then I'll put in an order for a McMuffin.

00:12:08.950 --> 00:12:11.810
Yikes, I'll be late.

00:12:11.810 --> 00:12:15.010
You don't have to visit if you're busy.

00:12:15.010 --> 00:12:18.560
But I want to come see you.

00:12:18.560 --> 00:12:20.510
Jeez, don't give me goosebumps!

00:12:23.630 --> 00:12:26.400
- Ayaka.
- Yes?

00:12:29.810 --> 00:12:31.410
See you around.

00:12:38.860 --> 00:12:42.510
[Search name: Ichika Kogo]

00:12:42.510 --> 00:12:44.830
[Driver's License: Ichika Kogo]

00:12:44.830 --> 00:12:48.830
The only things we got
are her license, and past records.

00:13:02.880 --> 00:13:06.650
[Plastic Surgeons]

00:13:09.310 --> 00:13:11.080
You're early today.

00:13:11.080 --> 00:13:13.100
Good morning.

00:13:14.260 --> 00:13:17.350
Hey, what's this?

00:13:17.350 --> 00:13:19.220
That's something Adachi's looking into.

00:13:19.220 --> 00:13:22.690
I wanted to consider the possibility
of Riku Hayase getting plastic surgery.

00:13:22.690 --> 00:13:24.600
Those are the clinics I'm investigating.

00:13:24.600 --> 00:13:26.340
Plastic surgery?

00:13:26.340 --> 00:13:29.520
No surgeon would see a wanted man.

00:13:29.520 --> 00:13:31.870
It's happened before.

00:13:31.870 --> 00:13:36.870
Besides, an investigator from our second team

00:13:36.870 --> 00:13:39.990
told me it happens often in the underworld.

00:13:39.990 --> 00:13:42.750
Apparently, it's called a "reboot" of sorts.

00:13:44.610 --> 00:13:48.230
You think a pâtissier has the connections
to make that happen?

00:13:48.230 --> 00:13:51.420
It's something I'll investigate in my own time.

00:13:51.420 --> 00:13:53.410
You sure love to take on extra work.

00:13:53.410 --> 00:13:54.820
Overtime's not for me.

00:13:54.820 --> 00:13:57.230
Could you two also look into this woman?

00:13:57.230 --> 00:13:58.900
[Ichika Kogo, Financial Advisor]

00:13:58.900 --> 00:14:00.520
"Ichika Kogo."

00:14:00.520 --> 00:14:03.760
GooSix's financial advisor?

00:14:03.760 --> 00:14:04.920
Yes.

00:14:04.920 --> 00:14:07.570
GooSix...

00:14:07.570 --> 00:14:12.310
They were Natsumi Hayase's clients.

00:14:12.310 --> 00:14:17.790
This Ichika Kogo took over
when Natsumi disappeared.

00:14:17.790 --> 00:14:21.880
I suspect she's involved somehow.

00:14:21.880 --> 00:14:25.070
What makes this company so suspicious?

00:14:25.070 --> 00:14:28.760
Natsumi Hayase assisted other companies.

00:14:29.680 --> 00:14:33.330
Call it a detective's hunch.

00:14:33.330 --> 00:14:35.000
Anyway, I'm counting on you two.

00:14:38.120 --> 00:14:40.400
There he goes again
with his detective's hunch.

00:14:40.400 --> 00:14:44.340
Inspector Gido has changed since he returned.

00:14:44.340 --> 00:14:47.530
I think he's always been a bit of an oddball.

00:14:47.530 --> 00:14:51.590
Let's just get this job done, okay?

00:14:55.850 --> 00:14:57.310
- Gido.
- Yes?

00:14:57.310 --> 00:14:59.130
Come here.

00:14:59.130 --> 00:15:02.440
- What is it, Sir?
- We sure drank our share yesterday.

00:15:02.440 --> 00:15:04.660
Aren't you hungover?

00:15:04.660 --> 00:15:06.400
Pardon?

00:15:08.050 --> 00:15:13.380
Sorry, but could we actually split the bill?

00:15:14.080 --> 00:15:16.940
I know I said it'd be my treat,

00:15:16.940 --> 00:15:20.120
but I forgot it's the wife's birthday this month.

00:15:20.120 --> 00:15:21.820
Mikami-san.

00:15:23.710 --> 00:15:26.280
We went drinking last night?

00:15:26.280 --> 00:15:30.840
What? You're the one who invited me.

00:15:32.500 --> 00:15:33.880
I-I did?

00:15:33.880 --> 00:15:37.350
Yes. Right as I was heading out of the office.

00:15:40.630 --> 00:15:44.110
I invited you, here. Right.

00:15:44.110 --> 00:15:46.720
How much do I owe you?

00:15:46.720 --> 00:15:49.350
20,000 yen, for two bars.

00:15:49.350 --> 00:15:51.830
I'm rounding down for you.

00:15:51.830 --> 00:15:54.980
Sir, what did we talk about again?

00:15:54.980 --> 00:15:59.010
Just about your recent work.

00:15:59.010 --> 00:16:02.990
You asked about the key to your locker, too.

00:16:03.840 --> 00:16:06.550
What, you don't remember?

00:16:06.550 --> 00:16:09.520
It's been a while since I drunk.

00:16:09.520 --> 00:16:11.170
Hold on.

00:16:13.800 --> 00:16:17.970
The lingerie bar's our secret, right?

00:16:17.970 --> 00:16:19.500
Of course.

00:16:47.040 --> 00:16:49.440
[Hayase]

00:16:50.860 --> 00:16:52.040
Hello?

00:16:52.040 --> 00:16:54.270
You were right.

00:16:54.270 --> 00:16:55.720
What?

00:16:57.070 --> 00:16:59.070
Gido is alive.

00:17:00.570 --> 00:17:03.260
He visited the office last night.

00:17:09.230 --> 00:17:11.260
Thank god...

00:17:11.260 --> 00:17:15.980
Mayu-san, if Gido contacts you, let me know.

00:17:16.680 --> 00:17:19.130
I won't do anything rash.

00:17:19.130 --> 00:17:22.030
I only wish to know what happened to my wife.

00:17:22.030 --> 00:17:25.080
Promise you'll keep me in the loop.

00:17:27.700 --> 00:17:29.670
Okay, I will.

00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:37.170
This proves Ichika-san was lying.

00:17:37.170 --> 00:17:40.550
What is going on here?

00:17:40.550 --> 00:17:44.510
She may have been working together with Gido.

00:17:44.510 --> 00:17:47.090
In any case, I'll continue looking into her.

00:17:48.900 --> 00:17:50.960
Please do.

00:17:53.970 --> 00:17:57.040
Hello there, Inspector Gido.

00:17:57.040 --> 00:17:59.910
Inspector General Makita.

00:17:59.910 --> 00:18:01.840
We often bump into each other, don't we?

00:18:01.840 --> 00:18:05.620
But of course. I have my eyes on you, after all.

00:18:06.620 --> 00:18:10.170
That doesn't bode well for my job, sir.

00:18:10.170 --> 00:18:13.990
Can't you at least be discreet about it?

00:18:13.990 --> 00:18:16.620
I feel like you're choking me out.

00:18:16.620 --> 00:18:21.750
You know that I like to fight head-on.

00:18:21.750 --> 00:18:24.230
So I can see how you'll react, you know?

00:18:24.230 --> 00:18:29.840
Might as well have fun on the job
if I have no hopes at a promotion.

00:18:29.840 --> 00:18:32.520
A fine motto, I'd say.

00:18:36.350 --> 00:18:38.750
Let's talk, shall we?

00:18:46.630 --> 00:18:48.980
You were searching our database earlier.

00:18:48.980 --> 00:18:53.270
And all those search records go to us.

00:18:53.270 --> 00:18:55.800
Why are you looking into this individual?

00:18:55.800 --> 00:18:59.500
To make sure justice is served, of course.

00:19:05.190 --> 00:19:08.210
You have ties to Fuyuhashi,

00:19:08.210 --> 00:19:13.170
and now you're looking into Goroku's people.

00:19:13.170 --> 00:19:15.090
I feel like I'm connecting dots here.

00:19:15.090 --> 00:19:20.610
I was only looking into her ties
with Natsumi Hayase.

00:19:20.610 --> 00:19:21.660
Right.

00:19:21.660 --> 00:19:27.740
I hear this "Natsumi Hayase"
was also a consultant for Goroku.

00:19:27.740 --> 00:19:31.890
I now see why you're invested in this case.

00:19:33.570 --> 00:19:35.320
It's a coincidence, Sir.

00:19:35.320 --> 00:19:38.430
It seems like I've backed you into a corner.

00:19:40.350 --> 00:19:42.390
It's a great look.

00:19:43.490 --> 00:19:47.150
Sir, could I get back to work? Duty calls.

00:19:47.150 --> 00:19:51.470
Right, of course. Your investigation awaits.

00:19:56.580 --> 00:20:00.810
You'd best eat well while you can, Inspector.

00:20:00.810 --> 00:20:04.310
The price of betrayal's a hefty one.

00:20:15.200 --> 00:20:16.600
So?

00:20:16.600 --> 00:20:19.480
He was most definitely lying, Sir.

00:20:25.100 --> 00:20:28.400
Now that's one dirty liar.

00:20:30.850 --> 00:20:36.000
I have to find Gido.
Ichika-san would know where to start.

00:20:40.000 --> 00:20:43.800
Kurehara-san, can I leave the vouchers to you?

00:20:43.800 --> 00:20:46.390
Sure thing.

00:20:56.100 --> 00:20:57.900
Ichika-san.

00:21:06.150 --> 00:21:08.200
What now?

00:21:09.630 --> 00:21:11.300
So...

00:21:14.300 --> 00:21:17.400
How about we go on a date?

00:21:17.400 --> 00:21:22.800
Well, not exactly a date.

00:21:22.800 --> 00:21:27.600
I just realized how little I know about you.

00:21:27.600 --> 00:21:30.500
We are supposed to be "lovers" and all.

00:21:30.500 --> 00:21:34.900
I really ought to have some knowledge
to back that claim.

00:21:35.700 --> 00:21:39.400
I'm on my way to do a job for Goroku.

00:21:40.400 --> 00:21:42.200
May I tag along?

00:21:42.200 --> 00:21:46.500
I'd like to see what your "jobs" entail.

00:21:48.860 --> 00:21:50.920
Come with me.

00:21:54.100 --> 00:21:56.700
- Hello there.
- Welcome.

00:21:56.700 --> 00:21:57.970
What is this place?

00:21:57.970 --> 00:22:00.080
- What?
- Are we on a date after all?

00:22:00.080 --> 00:22:03.080
No, this is all part of the job.

00:22:03.080 --> 00:22:06.790
Take your pick. I'll be buying a box or two.

00:22:08.360 --> 00:22:10.200
You have a sweet tooth to satiate, right?

00:22:10.200 --> 00:22:11.970
Right.

00:22:12.800 --> 00:22:15.820
- Hello, everyone.
- Hey there.

00:22:15.820 --> 00:22:17.100
Here, I brought donuts.

00:22:17.100 --> 00:22:19.320
- Thanks.
- Anytime.

00:22:19.320 --> 00:22:23.900
- Rikka, we got donuts.
- For real?

00:22:23.900 --> 00:22:25.780
Thank you so much!

00:22:25.780 --> 00:22:28.300
I didn't expect the plus one.
What's the occasion?

00:22:28.300 --> 00:22:31.000
We're having a date on the job.

00:22:33.440 --> 00:22:36.100
- Here are this week's results.
- How are we faring?

00:22:36.100 --> 00:22:38.500
- Can I borrow the office?
- Pretty well, I'd say.

00:22:38.500 --> 00:22:41.900
Feel free.
Kaieda's certainly not around to use it.

00:22:41.900 --> 00:22:43.900
Help yourselves to some coffee as well.

00:22:43.900 --> 00:22:45.800
Thanks.

00:22:47.460 --> 00:22:54.110
This law firm is a safe haven for victims
of scams and sketchy jobs.

00:22:55.870 --> 00:22:57.800
But that's only a front.

00:22:57.800 --> 00:23:02.300
Its true goal is to curate a roster
of those willing to partake in illicit work.

00:23:02.300 --> 00:23:04.100
A roster?

00:23:04.100 --> 00:23:09.400
The firm invites its clients
to partake in jobs of their own.

00:23:09.400 --> 00:23:12.900
Everyone falls for it
because they need the money.

00:23:12.900 --> 00:23:16.400
So once they're hooked, they can't go back?

00:23:16.400 --> 00:23:19.200
Terrifying.

00:23:19.200 --> 00:23:21.100
You're not going to eat your donut?

00:23:32.230 --> 00:23:35.430
That's sweet.

00:23:35.430 --> 00:23:37.880
I get why they're so popular.

00:23:37.880 --> 00:23:42.800
Is that the roster?

00:23:42.800 --> 00:23:47.100
We recruit individuals
from social media as well.

00:23:48.400 --> 00:23:53.400
Find people who need money,
then entice them with an opportunity.

00:23:53.400 --> 00:23:54.630
If we receive a response,
[Hey, I've got a job for you.]

00:23:54.630 --> 00:23:57.300
we ask for their ID and address,

00:23:57.300 --> 00:24:00.430
then ask them to download
a confidential messaging app.

00:24:00.430 --> 00:24:04.460
What sort of "jobs" are these people working?

00:24:04.460 --> 00:24:08.700
We have them make those accounts we use
for money laundering.

00:24:08.700 --> 00:24:13.100
One individual will make
about 10 different accounts.

00:24:13.100 --> 00:24:17.990
For that alone, they're paid about 10,000
to 50,000 yen per month.

00:24:17.990 --> 00:24:21.000
Won't those people think that's suspicious?

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:24.400
They have bigger problems to deal with.

00:24:24.400 --> 00:24:28.500
Even though the police crack down
on these sketchy jobs?

00:24:28.500 --> 00:24:33.400
People would do anything
for money they need to survive.

00:24:33.400 --> 00:24:37.010
Doesn't matter where you hail from.

00:24:37.010 --> 00:24:41.290
Poverty will always triumph rational thought.

00:24:41.290 --> 00:24:46.020
Some people try to quit, don't they?

00:24:46.020 --> 00:24:49.400
Of course. But if they ever try,
we threaten them.

00:24:49.400 --> 00:24:53.000
"We'll burn your house down."
"Say good bye to your family."

00:24:53.000 --> 00:24:58.300
That tends to work for most people.

00:24:58.300 --> 00:25:01.490
How horrible.

00:25:01.490 --> 00:25:05.880
You lose the will to resist
when family gets involved.

00:25:09.670 --> 00:25:12.160
That hits a bit too close to home.

00:25:13.230 --> 00:25:16.920
I mean, look at what I've done.

00:25:16.920 --> 00:25:18.610
Come in.

00:25:20.300 --> 00:25:22.000
Sorry to interrupt the date.

00:25:22.000 --> 00:25:24.010
Guess we're out of time.

00:25:24.010 --> 00:25:26.890
- Aki's on the line.
- All right.

00:25:28.340 --> 00:25:29.900
[Are you ready to join? Aki is on this call]

00:25:29.900 --> 00:25:31.800
You're in frame.

00:25:33.400 --> 00:25:34.800
Hi there, Ichika.

00:25:34.800 --> 00:25:36.850
Sorry for the short notice.

00:25:36.850 --> 00:25:39.190
It's fine. Is this about Sagami-Horai Bank?

00:25:39.190 --> 00:25:43.740
Yes. They've installed a chat-bot
to help filter out accounts.

00:25:43.740 --> 00:25:47.300
Ten of our applicants got rejected
because it asked for a company name.

00:25:47.300 --> 00:25:50.200
Grab the questions it asks.
We'll create a list of answers to give.

00:25:50.200 --> 00:25:55.730
Okay. TJ Trust wants to see proof
via a company website, too.

00:25:55.730 --> 00:25:57.610
What do we do about that?

00:25:59.480 --> 00:26:03.240
We'll have to create a website
for every fake company we have.

00:26:03.240 --> 00:26:07.060
It'll cost money and time
to outsource the work.

00:26:07.060 --> 00:26:09.000
Then we'll start a team of our own.

00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:11.800
We have the tools, it's not impossible.

00:26:11.800 --> 00:26:13.500
I'll see who we can use.

00:26:13.500 --> 00:26:15.100
I'll leave recruitment to you.

00:26:15.100 --> 00:26:17.950
Send me a word when you have a design.

00:26:17.950 --> 00:26:19.500
Yes, Ma'am.

00:26:19.500 --> 00:26:21.500
Talk to you later.

00:26:22.980 --> 00:26:25.480
That sounded so official.

00:26:25.480 --> 00:26:28.110
This is the general gist of my job.

00:26:28.110 --> 00:26:30.730
Or crime, if I wasn't sugarcoating it.

00:26:31.450 --> 00:26:34.030
Anything else you wanted to ask me?

00:26:34.030 --> 00:26:38.740
Ichika-san, you're the organization's treasurer.

00:26:38.740 --> 00:26:42.300
Does that mean you keep tabs
on all of their money?

00:26:42.300 --> 00:26:47.520
Yes, it's not too different
from normal accounting work.

00:26:48.200 --> 00:26:52.940
And you also deal with cash,
like the billion from three years ago?

00:26:52.940 --> 00:26:55.100
Sometimes.

00:26:55.100 --> 00:27:01.100
Do you still handle
that sort of physical capital?

00:27:02.000 --> 00:27:04.500
Come with me, I'll show you.

00:27:07.770 --> 00:27:11.700
This is the organization's secret safe.

00:27:11.700 --> 00:27:16.200
Though the big shots know it exists,
only Goroku and I know the location.

00:27:16.200 --> 00:27:17.500
Who brings the money here?

00:27:17.500 --> 00:27:19.100
Our part-timers.

00:27:19.100 --> 00:27:22.380
They're never told what they're transporting.

00:27:53.700 --> 00:27:55.300
Is this...

00:27:55.300 --> 00:27:59.900
Yes. They're currently filled with luxuries
gathered by a Hong Kong gang.

00:27:59.900 --> 00:28:01.500
"Luxuries"?

00:28:01.500 --> 00:28:06.600
Scammed prepaid cards,
stolen precious metals, the works.

00:28:06.600 --> 00:28:08.600
About how much is in here?

00:28:08.600 --> 00:28:12.900
Depends on the exchange rate,
but I'd estimate about ten billion yen.

00:28:12.900 --> 00:28:14.800
Ten billion?

00:28:14.800 --> 00:28:16.690
All this?

00:28:18.000 --> 00:28:20.100
Can I take a look inside?

00:28:34.180 --> 00:28:37.110
These goods will get liquidated to cash,

00:28:37.110 --> 00:28:40.970
then deposited to a bank overseas.

00:28:40.970 --> 00:28:44.500
With this much money,
you wouldn't even need to lift a finger.

00:28:44.500 --> 00:28:47.500
- You could say that again.
- But...

00:28:47.500 --> 00:28:52.930
He must really play the part
if you haven't caught on yet.

00:28:55.460 --> 00:28:59.450
It's a shame we gotta kill that Riku Hayase.

00:29:03.130 --> 00:29:04.500
[Hayase Patisserie]

00:29:04.500 --> 00:29:06.400
- Welcome.
- Hello there.

00:29:06.400 --> 00:29:08.990
Gido!

00:29:12.270 --> 00:29:15.750
I didn't realize your wife was a nutritionist.

00:29:15.750 --> 00:29:19.070
Her help has made all the difference.

00:29:19.070 --> 00:29:21.990
Thank you for sending her in to assist us.

00:29:21.990 --> 00:29:23.830
Sending her in?

00:29:23.830 --> 00:29:28.800
Your wife said you asked her to help out.

00:29:29.440 --> 00:29:32.360
- We're making pudding together.
- Pudding?

00:29:32.360 --> 00:29:36.230
It's an easy dessert to make in batches, no?

00:29:37.620 --> 00:29:39.300
Could we have a minute?

00:29:43.760 --> 00:29:48.260
I decided to take off my nutritionist work
and part time here for a while.

00:29:48.260 --> 00:29:51.400
Why?

00:29:51.400 --> 00:29:53.300
I felt like I owed you.

00:29:53.300 --> 00:29:55.800
I said you didn't need to feel responsible.

00:29:55.800 --> 00:29:59.420
Your mother is reaching her limits.

00:29:59.420 --> 00:30:02.050
The lack of sales
aren't helping her spirits, either.

00:30:02.050 --> 00:30:06.800
Won't my presence
be just the distraction she needs?

00:30:09.200 --> 00:30:15.200
Takumi-kun's doing his best
to recreate his father's pudding.

00:30:15.200 --> 00:30:18.480
Could you please tell us your recipe?

00:30:19.350 --> 00:30:22.790
[How to make a Hayase Pudding]

00:30:27.040 --> 00:30:31.600
Add about 15 grams more egg yolk.

00:30:31.600 --> 00:30:35.110
That egg flavor is what
makes our pudding a Hayase Pudding.

00:30:37.300 --> 00:30:39.220
All right.

00:30:48.470 --> 00:30:50.470
[I]

00:30:54.510 --> 00:30:58.260
Hello? Ichika-san?

00:30:59.540 --> 00:31:02.390
So this is what I sound like.

00:31:03.790 --> 00:31:05.710
Gido?

00:31:05.710 --> 00:31:07.600
Bingo.

00:31:07.600 --> 00:31:09.340
Where are you right now?

00:31:09.340 --> 00:31:12.290
I have questions.

00:31:12.290 --> 00:31:14.690
Listen up.

00:31:14.690 --> 00:31:19.290
Leave Mayu out of this. She's innocent.

00:31:26.200 --> 00:31:28.100
Your answer?

00:31:29.150 --> 00:31:30.760
I have no plan on getting her involved.

00:31:30.760 --> 00:31:34.240
Mayu-san is only helping the store
out of the kindness in her heart.

00:31:34.240 --> 00:31:35.940
Then have her quit, now.

00:31:35.940 --> 00:31:39.170
She's your wife, you convince her.

00:31:39.880 --> 00:31:42.490
Mayu-san is seriously worried about you.

00:31:42.490 --> 00:31:44.810
At least let her know you're safe.

00:31:44.810 --> 00:31:47.730
Worrying about others
when you're at risk yourself?

00:31:47.730 --> 00:31:50.870
Someone doesn't know how the world works.

00:31:51.590 --> 00:31:54.610
I know you murdered Natsumi.

00:31:54.610 --> 00:31:57.440
What have you done with Ichika-san?

00:31:57.440 --> 00:31:59.550
I'm sending you an address.

00:31:59.550 --> 00:32:02.510
Come, and I'll give you answers.

00:32:04.610 --> 00:32:07.620
[Address Link]

00:32:26.630 --> 00:32:28.340
Gido?

00:32:33.910 --> 00:32:35.800
I'm here.

00:32:41.140 --> 00:32:43.150
Gido?

00:32:57.310 --> 00:33:00.500
Fuyuhashi? Why are you...

00:33:04.300 --> 00:33:06.790
Where's the merchandise?

00:33:06.790 --> 00:33:11.380
Mr. Ma left it with us for safekeeping.
Now, where is it?

00:33:11.380 --> 00:33:13.440
What are you talking about?

00:33:24.270 --> 00:33:25.980
No.

00:33:25.980 --> 00:33:27.050
You've been set up.

00:33:27.050 --> 00:33:29.980
We confirmed this video's the real deal.

00:33:29.980 --> 00:33:32.680
You're guilty as charged.

00:33:32.680 --> 00:33:37.730
We'll uncover your tracks
even if you choose to remain silent.

00:33:38.530 --> 00:33:42.360
And if silence is your answer, so be it.

00:33:43.880 --> 00:33:46.880
But I will ask you one last time.

00:33:46.880 --> 00:33:50.060
Where did you put the ten billion yen?

00:34:10.890 --> 00:34:13.340
I'm not Gido!

00:34:14.880 --> 00:34:16.990
I'm Riku Hayase.

00:34:17.740 --> 00:34:19.510
Riku Hayase?

00:34:19.510 --> 00:34:23.730
I only look like Gido
because of plastic surgery.

00:34:23.730 --> 00:34:26.650
The one in the video is the real deal.

00:34:34.820 --> 00:34:37.050
How fascinating!

00:34:37.050 --> 00:34:41.000
Men sure make interesting excuses
when their lives are on the line.

00:34:41.000 --> 00:34:43.410
I rebooted!

00:34:44.310 --> 00:34:48.660
I assume you two have heard the term before.

00:34:51.640 --> 00:34:53.450
Sir, please.

00:34:54.430 --> 00:34:57.540
Please, let me prove myself.

00:34:57.540 --> 00:35:02.150
Let me prove I'm Riku Hayase.

00:35:39.940 --> 00:35:43.180
I'm always the one making the final meals.

00:35:43.930 --> 00:35:47.100
I've never been on the other side of things.

00:35:49.380 --> 00:35:52.650
Don't be so antsy.
This is an interesting turn of events.

00:35:52.650 --> 00:35:56.490
The real Gido was no cook.

00:35:56.490 --> 00:35:58.040
He disliked sweet things as well.

00:35:58.040 --> 00:36:02.450
You're saying baking a dessert
proves you're not Gido?

00:36:02.450 --> 00:36:07.010
I ran a family patisserie of 48 years.

00:36:07.010 --> 00:36:09.880
I am a professional at work.

00:36:09.880 --> 00:36:12.680
I will put everything I am into this cake.

00:37:01.140 --> 00:37:03.610
Here is my specialty, a Hayase Shortcake.

00:37:03.610 --> 00:37:06.620
Though the cake would usually cool for a bit,

00:37:06.620 --> 00:37:11.350
the recipe itself, I inherited from my father.

00:37:11.350 --> 00:37:13.070
Please, enjoy.

00:37:52.720 --> 00:37:54.530
No, not that.

00:37:55.870 --> 00:37:57.930
Have a bite.

00:38:21.560 --> 00:38:26.190
A pâtissier wouldn't have the connections
necessary for a reboot.

00:38:26.960 --> 00:38:29.140
Who helped you?

00:38:31.470 --> 00:38:33.340
Ichika?

00:38:35.700 --> 00:38:38.210
She's currently getting treated
at a hospital.

00:38:38.210 --> 00:38:39.900
Call her here.

00:38:45.170 --> 00:38:47.070
Kiriya here.

00:38:47.070 --> 00:38:48.810
Bring us Ichika-san.

00:38:48.810 --> 00:38:51.380
Well, I would, but...

00:39:02.580 --> 00:39:04.530
Have a seat.

00:39:15.550 --> 00:39:18.530
He says he got a reboot.

00:39:18.530 --> 00:39:21.350
I suspect you helped him.

00:39:24.700 --> 00:39:28.040
Speak, or you'll disappear with him.

00:39:32.540 --> 00:39:37.170
Three years ago, Gido stole the billion,

00:39:37.170 --> 00:39:40.700
murdered Natsumi-san, and then buried her.

00:39:40.700 --> 00:39:43.310
Gido was behind it all?

00:39:45.160 --> 00:39:47.440
Yes. He told me himself.

00:39:47.440 --> 00:39:50.060
Why didn't you say anything?

00:39:53.410 --> 00:39:55.180
Keep going.

00:39:57.100 --> 00:40:01.410
Gido also came to me

00:40:01.410 --> 00:40:04.050
to embezzle money from the organization.

00:40:04.050 --> 00:40:06.260
And you obliged?

00:40:11.600 --> 00:40:16.200
He threatened to kill my sister.
I had no choice.

00:40:19.940 --> 00:40:26.300
Gido was on the verge of arrest
with the Inspector General hot on his tail.

00:40:26.300 --> 00:40:29.700
That was when Natsumi-san's body was found,

00:40:29.700 --> 00:40:34.160
and Goroku-san began pressing Gido.

00:40:35.030 --> 00:40:37.900
At his wits' end,

00:40:37.900 --> 00:40:41.000
Gido came to me with a proposal.

00:40:42.460 --> 00:40:44.340
His plan...

00:40:45.100 --> 00:40:49.500
was to pressure Riku Hayase-san into a corner

00:40:50.200 --> 00:40:53.100
and have him reboot as "Gido."

00:40:57.790 --> 00:41:02.780
I followed his plan and tricked you.

00:41:04.200 --> 00:41:10.510
Gido planned to escape overseas
once Hayase-san began acting as "Gido."

00:41:11.200 --> 00:41:15.880
He was to lie low
until the organization was off his trail.

00:41:17.370 --> 00:41:19.910
But instead,

00:41:19.910 --> 00:41:23.840
he double-crossed me
and made off with another 10 billion.

00:41:25.700 --> 00:41:29.000
I believe this was his plan from the start.

00:41:30.000 --> 00:41:33.600
He hoped to pin all the blame on Hayase-san

00:41:33.600 --> 00:41:36.350
and make off with the fortune.

00:41:39.850 --> 00:41:43.430
Sounds utterly unbelievable.

00:41:45.640 --> 00:41:48.400
Please, allow me to prove myself.

00:41:48.400 --> 00:41:50.400
Prove yourself?

00:41:53.410 --> 00:41:56.310
I will bring you the real Gido.

00:42:00.540 --> 00:42:05.600
♫ It just wears down little by little ♫

00:42:05.600 --> 00:42:07.190
♫ It just wears down your heart ♫

00:42:07.190 --> 00:42:12.510
♫ It just wears down your heart ♫

00:42:16.480 --> 00:42:19.860
Your cake tastes fine,
if not a bit old-fashioned.

00:42:20.530 --> 00:42:23.830
It's what makes our cakes special.

00:42:23.830 --> 00:42:27.590
My wife loved that nostalgic taste.

00:42:31.720 --> 00:42:34.500
You have until midnight tomorrow.

00:42:36.120 --> 00:42:38.410
Ichika-san.

00:42:38.410 --> 00:42:42.610
If you find nothing,
this will be goodbye to you as well.

00:42:43.740 --> 00:42:48.470
♫ Just paint over each day ♫

00:42:48.470 --> 00:42:50.260
♫ Just paint over it desperately ♫

00:42:50.260 --> 00:42:55.500
♫ Just paint over it desperately ♫

00:42:55.500 --> 00:42:56.740
♫ In reality ♫

00:42:56.740 --> 00:43:01.910
♫ It just becomes empty ♫

00:43:01.910 --> 00:43:03.550
♫ My heart just becomes empty ♫

00:43:03.550 --> 00:43:08.830
♫ My heart just becomes empty ♫

00:43:10.160 --> 00:43:15.430
♫ "Are you laughing more than usual?" ♫

00:43:15.430 --> 00:43:18.640
You won't condemn me for tricking you?

00:43:20.930 --> 00:43:23.420
♫ Did such a day even exist? ♫

00:43:23.420 --> 00:43:30.570
♫ The treasure that shines in my heart ♫

00:43:30.570 --> 00:43:35.170
He threatened you with Ayaka-san's life.

00:43:37.860 --> 00:43:42.560
It's only obvious you would do anything
to protect your family.

00:43:45.390 --> 00:43:47.790
Here, try a slice.

00:43:47.790 --> 00:43:50.250
The Hayase Shortcake.

00:43:52.300 --> 00:43:56.300
The strawberry on top

00:43:56.300 --> 00:43:59.410
makes the cake taste all the sweeter.

00:44:10.580 --> 00:44:13.930
That's how Natsumi always ate her slice.

00:44:24.590 --> 00:44:26.920
I'll pass.

00:44:26.920 --> 00:44:29.080
Why?

00:44:29.080 --> 00:44:31.340
Because this cake is Natsumi-san's.

00:44:43.180 --> 00:44:48.730
I can finally avenge Natsumi.

00:44:56.610 --> 00:44:59.330
I can return to Takumi-kun.

00:45:06.100 --> 00:45:09.130
I'm coming home, Natsumi.

00:45:09.130 --> 00:45:19.200
Timing and subtitles by
"🍰 The Pastry Detectives 🔍" Team @Viki.com

00:45:19.200 --> 00:45:21.500
Let's settle this.

00:45:22.540 --> 00:45:24.140
Yes.

00:45:31.290 --> 00:45:35.500
[Reboot]

00:45:35.500 --> 00:45:38.420
- You seriously look like me.
- Traitor.

00:45:38.420 --> 00:45:41.500
Bring me the goods. Or else your sister's dead.
[Next time, Episode 5: Decisive Battle]

00:45:41.500 --> 00:45:43.700
Please, tell us the truth.
[Gido vs Hayase]

00:45:43.700 --> 00:45:45.100
For your future's sake.
[Gido's rampage goes on]

00:45:45.100 --> 00:45:47.200
Looks like you've got grand ambitions, kid.

00:45:47.200 --> 00:45:50.200
- Why are you working for him?
- For money, why else?

00:45:50.200 --> 00:45:51.700
I have to protect this store.
[Hayase's memories of the past... what are his true feelings?]

00:45:51.700 --> 00:45:53.000
I have to return to my family,
[The time limit to get to his family is approaching.]

00:45:53.000 --> 00:45:55.600
no matter the cost.

00:45:55.600 --> 00:45:57.600
You murdered Natsumi, didn't you?
[A battle of the lookalikes]

00:45:57.600 --> 00:45:58.740
Answer me!
[A battle of the lookalikes]